{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879716934,"sessionID":"ses_28553eea1ffeDmn01asoGfwPHq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aacebc0001EDjH0Kt0KG44JF","messageID":"msg_d7aacd28e001MHe8bTe9c6TH56","sessionID":"ses_28553eea1ffeDmn01asoGfwPHq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018\n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n**Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n- **AND** the agentd manager is running\n- **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the change\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked with the object's namespace and name\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox deletion triggers reconcile\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is deleted from the cluster\n- **AND** the agentd manager is running\n- **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the deletion\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked to handle cleanup\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Idle Detection Input\n\nThe system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue.\n\n#### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists without the `last-activity-time` annotation\n- **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n- **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty annotation value means no deletion\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists with `last-activity-time` annotation set to empty string\n- **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n- **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Idle Detection Parsing\n\nWhen the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid RFC3339 timestamp parses successfully\n- **GIVEN** annotation value is a valid RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\")\n- **WHEN** `time.Parse` is called\n- **THEN** the timestamp SHALL be parsed successfully\n- **AND** reconciliation SHALL proceed to expiration check\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues with error\n- **GIVEN** annotation value is not a valid RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., \"invalid-time\")\n- **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n- **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n- **AND** the error SHALL be logged\n\n#### Scenario: Malformed timestamp requeues\n- **GIVEN** annotation value is malformed (e.g., \"2024-13-45T99:99:99Z\")\n- **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n- **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Expiration Threshold\n\nThe system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n\n#### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n- **AND** `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n- **AND** `time.Now()` is after `expirationTime`\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL call delete on the `Sandbox` resource\n- **AND** on success, reconcile SHALL return empty result with nil error\n\n#### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n- **AND** `expirationTime = lastActivity + 15 minutes`\n- **AND** `time.Now()` is before `expirationTime`\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)`\n- **AND** no delete SHALL occur\n\n#### Scenario: Exactly at expiration triggers delete\n- **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is exactly 15 minutes ago\n- **AND** `time.Now()` equals `expirationTime`\n- **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n- **THEN** the controller SHALL call delete on the `Sandbox` resource\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Delete Idempotency\n\nWhen delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n\n#### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox handled gracefully\n- **GIVEN** the API server returns `NotFound` on delete\n- **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n- **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n- **AND** no error SHALL be logged\n\n#### Scenario: Delete conflict returns error for retry\n- **GIVEN** the API server returns a conflict error on delete\n- **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n- **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, err)`\n- **AND** controller-runtime SHALL retry with backoff\n\n#### Scenario: Delete network error returns error for retry\n- **GIVEN** the API server returns a connection error on delete\n- **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n- **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, err)`\n- **AND** controller-runtime SHALL retry with backoff\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Get Not Found Handling\n\nWhen get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n- **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists when Get is called\n- **AND** the API server returns `NotFound`\n- **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n- **THEN** reconcile SHALL return `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)` without error\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Manager Configuration\n\nThe `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n\n#### Scenario: Manager starts with correct configuration\n- **GIVEN** the scheme contains core Kubernetes types\n- **AND** the scheme contains `sandboxv1alpha1` types\n- **AND** metrics server is disabled\n- **AND** health probe server is disabled\n- **WHEN** the manager is created\n- **THEN** the manager SHALL start without error\n\n#### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n- **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n- **WHEN** SIGTERM or SIGINT is received\n- **THEN** the manager SHALL stop gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n\n---\n\n## Changes to Base Specification\n\nThis AR implements the Agentd idle cleanup controller using the client-go library interfaces defined in deployment/client-go.md. No modifications to existing interfaces.\n\n---\n\n## New Interfaces\n\n### Reconciler Interface\n\n```go\npackage agentd\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/controller/controllerutil\"\n    ctrl \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n)\n\n// SessionExpirationTimeout defines the idle timeout before sandbox deletion\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n\n// Reconciler reconciles Sandbox objects for idle cleanup\ntype Reconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n}\n\n// Reconcile implements the idle cleanup logic\nfunc (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n\n// SetupWithManager sets up the controller with the Manager\nfunc (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n```\n\n### Main Entry Point\n\n```go\n// cmd/agentd/main.go\n\n// Scheme registration\nvar schemeBuilder = runtime.NewSchemeBuilder()\n\nfunc init() {\n    utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n    utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n}\n\n// main creates and runs the controller-runtime manager\nfunc main()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Modified Interfaces\n\nNone. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n\n---\n\n## Behavioral Changes\n\n| Behavior | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| Sandbox lifecycle | No automatic cleanup | Automatic deletion after 15 min idle |\n| Resource tracking | No activity tracking | last-activity-time annotation read |\n| Reconciliation | N/A | Controller-runtime reconciler watches Sandboxes |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.x | Controller-runtime framework |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Local | Sandbox CRD types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | v0.x | Kubernetes API errors |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | v0.x | Kubernetes runtime types |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Local | Annotation key constants |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated client (base spec) |\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation with idle cleanup logic |\n| `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` | Unit tests for reconciler |\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Binary entry point and manager setup |\n\n---\n\n## Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `SessionExpirationTimeout` | `15 * time.Minute` | Idle timeout before sandbox deletion |\n| `RequeueAfterParseError` | `30 * time.Second` | Requeue delay when timestamp parse fails |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\nNone. The controller uses hardcoded constants for configuration.\n\n### Annotations Read\n\n| Annotation Key | Source | Description |\n|---------------|--------|-------------|\n| `last-activity-time` | `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` | RFC3339 timestamp of last sandbox activity |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints Summary\n\nThis AR is a controller (reconciler) that watches Kubernetes resources; no new API endpoints are exposed.\n\n---\n\n## Watched Resources\n\n| API Group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n|-----------|---------|------|---------|\n| `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Create, Update, Delete |\n\nNo explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n\n---\n\n## Migration Notes\n\n- Ensure `sandboxv1alpha1` scheme is registered before starting the manager\n- The workload manager must set `last-activity-time` annotation on Sandboxes for cleanup to function\n- Existing Sandboxes without the annotation will not be cleaned up\n- Deploy agentd binary alongside other agentcube components\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n1. **Reconciliation**: Controller-runtime reconciler registered for Sandbox resources\n2. **Annotation Reading**: Correctly reads `last-activity-time` annotation from Sandbox metadata\n3. **Timestamp Parsing**: Parses RFC3339 timestamps; handles parse errors with 30s requeue\n4. **Expiration Logic**: Correctly computes expiration time (lastActivity + 15 minutes)\n5. **Idle Detection**: Deletes sandboxes idle for more than 15 minutes\n6. **Future Requeue**: Requeues with appropriate delay when expiration is in the future\n7. **Idempotency**: Handles NotFound errors gracefully (no error returned)\n8. **Error Handling**: Returns errors for retry on transient failures\n9. **Manager Setup**: Correctly configures controller-runtime manager with scheme\n10. **Signal Handling**: Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n11. **Unit Tests**: >85% coverage on reconciler logic\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775879716924,"end":1775879716932}}}}
