{"type":"text","timestamp":1775879752119,"sessionID":"ses_28553eea1ffeDmn01asoGfwPHq","part":{"id":"prt_d7aae6c36001nWCCw7qZ0pCXjE","messageID":"msg_d7aae4478001ewn7ALTzDNpRyR","sessionID":"ses_28553eea1ffeDmn01asoGfwPHq","type":"text","text":"I've successfully created the delta-spec.md file for AR-018 (Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller) at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md`.\n\nThe specification includes:\n\n**Requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios:**\n- **Reconciliation Trigger**: Controller-runtime reconciler for Sandbox resources\n- **Idle Detection Input**: Reading `last-activity-time` annotation\n- **Idle Detection Parsing**: RFC3339 timestamp parsing with 30s requeue on error\n- **Expiration Threshold**: 15-minute idle timeout with delete logic\n- **Delete Idempotency**: Handling NotFound errors gracefully\n- **Get Not Found Handling**: Empty result when Sandbox removed\n- **Manager Configuration**: Controller-runtime manager setup\n\n**New Interfaces:**\n- `Reconciler` struct with `Reconcile()` and `SetupWithManager()` methods\n- `cmd/agentd/main.go` entry point\n\n**Key specifications:**\n- `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n- `RequeueAfterParseError = 30 * time.Second`\n- Uses `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` for annotation reading\n- Watches `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/Sandbox` resources\n\nThe spec follows the OpenSpec format with 11 acceptance criteria covering reconciliation, annotation reading, timestamp parsing, expiration logic, idempotency, error handling, and testing requirements.","time":{"start":1775879752116,"end":1775879752116}}}
